defs.docs:
NeuRacle is a Layer 2 solution that provide 
 decentralized, trustless data validation service 
 to bring off-chain data into Radix Ledger.
 
 NeuRacle is inspired by [Komodo Trustless Oracles](https://komodoplatform.com/en/blog/the-promise-of-smart-contracts-and-the-oracle-problem/)
 to use Consensus Models for validating data 
 off-chain and bring on-chain.
 
 The solution is using a Consensus Models, however, not
 every Consensus solved the Blockchain trilemma. 
 The more security, decentralized that Oracles has, 
 the harder it come to finality on each data validation,
 destroy the liveness of data stream.

attributes.value: / NeuRacle is a Layer 2 solution that provide
/ to bring off-chain data into Radix Ledger.
/ to use Consensus Models for validating data
/ The solution is using a Consensus Models, however, not
/ every Consensus solved the Blockchain trilemma.
/ The more security, decentralized that Oracles has,
/ the harder it come to finality on each data validation,
/ destroy the liveness of data stream.
/ Thus, NeuRacle will utilize the atomic-composability and
/ unlimited scalability trait of Radix Ledger to bring data validation
/ This is only a NeuRacle prototype that work with-out sharding.

defs.name: datas
defs.docs: Store NeuRacle validated datas.

defs.name: stable_coins
defs.docs: Store L2 stable coins project and it's name

defs.name: validators
defs.docs: NeuRacle Validators and their vote weight (staked amount).

defs.name: validator_cap
defs.docs: The maximum validator will be choosed to validate data and mint reward per data feeding round

defs.name: controller_badge
defs.docs: NeuRacle component controller badge, this can also be used to control other project in NeuRacle L2

defs.name: pay_rate
defs.docs: The rate which user has to pay per data feeding round. All will be burned.

defs.name: fee_stablecoin
defs.docs: The fee user has to pay for ecosystem when using L2 stablecoin project of NeuRacle. All will be burned.

defs.name: unstake_delay
defs.docs: Unstaking will be delayed for an amount of time before withdrawal.

defs.name: stage
defs.docs: After having a good decentralization and security, Admin can advance stage to allow anyone can become validator.

defs.name: round_length
defs.docs: The frequent of data feeding. Current Scrypto version only allow using epoch time unit, so the lowest is 1 epoch, estimated 1 hour per data update.

defs.name: reward_rate
defs.docs: The inflation percent each round. If reward_rate is 0.0015% and 1 round = 1 epoch ~ 1 hour, that's about 13.14% APY.

defs.name: punishment
defs.docs: Untruthful validator behavior will be punished * times per reward rate. Eg: punishment = 5, reward rate = 0.0015 > punish 0.0075% per round.

defs.name: system_time
defs.docs: NeuRacle system time, caculated by current epoch / round length.

defs.name: round_start
defs.docs: Keep track of the round status.

defs.name: active_validators
defs.docs: Keep track of the active validators per round.

defs.name: mint_controller_badge
defs.docs: The badge to mint new NeuRacle ecosystem controller badge when new L2 project created.
